details:
Case 206 is an imported case involving a 33 year-old female New Zealand national who is a Singapore Long Term Visit Pass holder, and had been to the United States from 28 February to 13 March. She is currently warded in an isolation room at NCID.

She reported onset of symptoms on 12 March, and had sought treatment at a GP clinic on 13 March. She was referred to NCID on the same day. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 14 March morning.

Prior to hospital admission, she mostly stayed at her home at Upper Paya Lebar Road.
